March 2026
  2.0.0 Full ground-up rewrite of the Electron ATM Emulator (V2)

  ─── ARCHITECTURE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * Converted project to an npm workspaces monorepo under `electron-atm-v2/`
  * Project split into three independently buildable packages:
      @atm/protocol  — pure NDC protocol layer (parser, builder, crypto, types)
      @atm/core      — ATM state machine and hardware simulation layer
      @atm/desktop   — Electron + React front-end application
  * Strict dependency hierarchy enforced: protocol → core → desktop
  * Requires Node.js >= 20.0.0
  * All packages authored as ES Modules (`"type": "module"`)
  * Project-wide base TypeScript configuration via `tsconfig.base.json`

  ─── LANGUAGE & TYPE SAFETY ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * Migrated entire codebase from JavaScript (ES6) to TypeScript 5.x
  * All public APIs and internal types fully typed; no implicit `any`
  * Shared type definitions centralised in `@atm/protocol/src/types/`
  * Eliminated all legacy CommonJS `require()` calls; ESM `import`/`export`
    used throughout
  * Strict null checks and strict mode enabled across all packages

  ─── @atm/protocol PACKAGE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * NDC message parser extracted from the monolithic codebase and rewritten
    in strict TypeScript with fully typed return values
  * NDC message builder extracted and rewritten; produces typed message frames
  * Cryptographic routines (PIN-block, DES/3DES, key management) ported to
    TypeScript and placed in `src/crypto/`
  * Removed runtime dependency on `ndc-parser`, `atm-screentext`,
    `atm-cursor`, `pinblock`, `atm-opcode-buffer`, `atm-fits`,
    `atm-screens`, `atm-states`, and `atm-hardware` npm modules — all
    functionality is now owned and maintained within the monorepo
  * Package exports a clean public API via `src/index.ts`

  ─── @atm/core PACKAGE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * ATM state machine rebuilt using XState v5 (`xstate@^5.28.0`)
      - Fully declarative state chart defined in `atmMachine.ts`
      - All state-type processing logic (states A–Y) ported to
        `stateProcessor.ts`; each state handler is an isolated, testable
        function
  * Hardware abstraction layer introduced:
      - `interfaces.ts` defines `IHardware` contract for peripherals
      - `mockHardware.ts` provides a fully simulated hardware implementation
        that covers card reader, receipt printer, journal printer, and cash
        dispenser for emulator operation without real hardware
      - `supplyCounters.ts` tracks cassette levels, reject counts, and
        dispense operations with full NDC Supply Counter message support
  * Host communication layer extracted to `src/host/` with dedicated TCP
    socket management, connection lifecycle handling, and NDC message framing
  * Package exports a typed public API via `src/index.ts`
  * Unit tests written with Vitest (`vitest@^2.1.2`)

  ─── @atm/desktop PACKAGE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * Electron upgraded to v40 (`electron@^40.6.1`)
  * Renderer process rebuilt as a React 19 Single-Page Application
  * Build tooling replaced: Vite 7 (`vite@^7.3.1`) replaces the legacy
    Electron-builder/Webpack pipeline; `@vitejs/plugin-react` used for JSX
    transform
  * Tailwind CSS v3 (`tailwindcss@^3.4.19`) + PostCSS + Autoprefixer replace
    Bootstrap for styling
  * shadcn/ui component primitives integrated via Radix UI:
      - `@radix-ui/react-dialog`   — modal dialogs
      - `@radix-ui/react-label`    — accessible label elements
      - `@radix-ui/react-slot`     — polymorphic component composition
      - `@radix-ui/react-switch`   — toggle switch controls
  * `class-variance-authority`, `clsx`, and `tailwind-merge` used for
    class composition and conditional styling
  * `lucide-react` icon library replaces legacy Font Awesome usage
  * `uuid` library used for unique card and session ID generation
  * XState Store (`@xstate/store@^3.16.0`) used for lightweight UI state
    management alongside the core XState machine
  * Interactive state-flow graph rendered with `@xyflow/react@^12.10.1`

  ─── USER INTERFACE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * New top-level tab navigation with dedicated tabs:
      Emulator | States | Screens | FITs | EMV | Cards | Hardware
  * Emulator tab:
      - ATMLayout component renders the persistent ATM screen with realistic
        bezel framing and dynamic screen content driven by the state machine
      - ATMKeypad component provides FDK buttons, numeric PIN pad, Enter,
        Cancel, and Clear keys; keyboard shortcut support preserved
      - NDC message log pane (`NdcLog.tsx`) rendered persistently at the
        bottom of the Emulator view
  * Inspector panels (all new components):
      - StatesPanel  — tabular state list, state search, current/exit state
                       highlighting, per-state screen and opcode preview
      - StateGraph   — interactive visual graph of all state transitions
                       rendered with React Flow / XY Flow
      - ScreensPanel — lists all downloaded screen definitions with preview
      - FitsPanel    — FIT record table showing institution ID, card ranges,
                       and processing flags
      - EmvPanel     — display of received EMV configuration data
      - CardsPanel   — full card management UI: create card, edit card,
                       select card for transaction, payment scheme detection
                       by BIN, swipe simulation
      - HardwarePanel — live view of simulated hardware component status
                        (card reader, receipt printer, journal printer,
                        cassette levels, reject bin)
      - StatusBar    — persistent status bar showing connection state, ATM
                       operational mode, current state and screen, LUNO, and
                       real-time message coordination number
  * Profile selection screen (`SetupScreen`) on startup allowing users to
    save, load, and manage named ATM configuration profiles
  * Dynamic screen rendering: screens are composed from NDC ESC-sequence
    actions (clear_screen, insert_image, position text, colour/blink control)
    driven by data received from the host in real time

  ─── DEVELOPER EXPERIENCE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * Test framework replaced: Vitest replaces Jasmine/Ava
  * End-to-end test capability added via Playwright (`@playwright/test@^1.48`)
  * `tsx` added for running TypeScript scripts directly without pre-compiling
  * Scripts: `npm run build` builds all packages; `npm start` launches
    Electron; `npm test` runs Vitest unit tests per package
  * Incremental TypeScript builds via `tsconfig.tsbuildinfo` in each package
  * Consistent ESLint configuration enforced across the monorepo

  ─── REMOVED / DEPRECATED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
  * Removed jQuery dependency
  * Removed Bootstrap CSS framework
  * Removed vis.js (state graph now uses React Flow / XY Flow)
  * Removed all inline `atm-*` npm module dependencies (rolled into monorepo)
  * Removed `jasmine` and `ava` test runners
  * Legacy `src/` directory and `index.html` (v1 app) remain in the root for
    reference but are no longer the active application

